Disney's "Once Upon a Studio" celebrates 100 years of magic with an iconic tribute to Robin Williams

Disney Animation has created an animated short called "Once Upon a Studio" to pay tribute to its rich legacy and iconic characters. The film features characters like Snow White, Peter Pan, and Genie, and was meticulously hand-drawn by a team of animators. The directors aimed to make each character appear as if they had just stepped out of their respective movies. The film also includes the voices of over 40 original voice actors, including Robin Williams as the Genie.

Robin Williams's daughter Zelda voices concerns over AI replication of father, says it's a violation of human creativity

Zelda Williams, daughter of the late Robin Williams, has criticized the use of artificial intelligence (AI) to replicate her father, calling it a "Frankensteinian monster" and personally disturbing. She expressed concern over non-consensual AI replications and the impact on living actors who should have the opportunity to create characters with their own choices and efforts.
